<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="847" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d847">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2491/48.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Squiers</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-30"><hi rend="italic">December 30,
                                    1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 143.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your telegram of the 24th
                            instant, I inclose a copy<note n="1" xml:id="d847fn1">Supra.</note> of a
                            note from the Costa Rican special envoy, in which he states the
                            questions relating to the disputed territory between Costa Rica and
                            Panama which his Government desires submitted to a new arbitration.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>